To fix the code quality issue of having a console.log statement in production code, you should remove or comment out the console.log statement.

Before fixing:
```typescript
// src\app\api\setup-database\route.ts

// other code here

console.log("Database setup successful!");
```

After fixing:
```typescript
// src\app\api\setup-database\route.ts

// other code here

// console.log("Database setup successful!");
```

By commenting out the console.log statement, it will no longer be executed in the production code, but you can still keep it in the code for future reference or debugging purposes. Remember to avoid using console.log statements in production code to maintain code cleanliness and to prevent potential security risks.